[5] Cholera - South Africa (KwaZulu-Natal province)
Date: Fri 2 Mar 2018
Source: Zululand Observer [edited]
https://zululandobserver.co.za/166139/confirmed-cholera-case-umkhanyakude/


The uMkhanyakude District Environmental Health Department has embarked on an awareness campaign following a confirmed case of cholera in the district. The patient, a woman from the Makanisi area, became infected after drinking contaminated water she collected from the Pongola River. She was successfully treated at Manguzi Hospital.

According to national guidelines, a single case of cholera is regarded as an outbreak, so the district is taking all precautions necessary.

[Byline: Tamlyn Jolly]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[uMkhanyakude is the northernmost of the 11 districts of the KwaZulu-Natal province of South Africa. Its seat is Mkuze. The area can be found on a map at: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Umkhanyakude_District_Municipality. - Mod.LL]

